        "text": "Issues of where hypertext systems should store their links are currently being debated within the hypertext community. Paths present similar issues. A path mechanism can store its path links with other hypertext links, or it can store its path links separately. In either case, the information stored must support path playback and path visualization. Figure 1 displays two paths expressed in three ways: as embedded links, as a separate textual path, and as a separategraphical path."
